product_description: From toggles to pushbuttons, rockers to micro switches, APEM develops and produces one of the widest ranges of interfaces dedicated to panels.
Maximum locking force and compact packaging combined with the industry’s best strength-to-size ratio make this switch ideal for safeguarding machinery and equipment.
The IDEC SE2L safety laser scanner is the smallest in the world, while outperforming most of the competition. Features include a 270-degree sensing angle

The HS6B is the smallest three-contact enabling switch currently on the market, and will fit in even the tightest areas, so you have safety in every necessary location.

Building on a long history of pushbutton dominance, IDEC offers its internationally rated 22mm pushbuttons and pilot devices, the HW series.
With a choice of metallic or black plastic bezels, and flush or standard mounting, our newest 16mm switches add style and safety to any application.
The A6 series of pushbuttons and pilot devices offer a very competitive price and simple construction in a space saving package.
DIN rail mount with finger safe spring up screw terminals and trip current ratings up to 30A. Available in 1, 2 or 3 poles. Optional direct panel mount kit available.
The NRA series of circuit breakers offer the ultimate in flexibility. Different actuator styles allow for differentiation of look and feel.
The NRBM series of circuit breakers feature stud termination for extra reliability in terminating wires.
